<item>
            <title>[LU-11804] Auto tune cpu partitions for high IOPS workload</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11804</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are number of IOPS related performance impromvenss in Lustre-2.12 that are not only server side, but also client side. Attached resutls is 4K random read IOPS on single client.&lt;br/&gt;
There is 40% performance improvmtns with default client setting in lustre-2.12, but after tune incresing of cpu partitions, IOPS bumps up a lot.&lt;br/&gt;
This is great improvements, but I am still wondering if we should have auto tuning of cpu partition on such high IOPS workload with out of the box.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
